    "cd_t_329": "Research translated into classroom practice — each article clearly states the evidence base and implementation steps.",
    "cd_t_330": "Free Marzano resources on instructional strategies — nine high-yield strategies grounded in 35 years of classroom research.",
    "cd_t_331": "US government's free education research hub — ERIC database, practice guides and What Works Clearinghouse all in one place.",
    "cd_t_332": "Daily 3-question teacher survey + weekly PD content — see how 10,000+ colleagues respond and benchmark your own views.",
    "cd_t_333": "Free forums for every subject and age range — resource sharing, advice threads and career discussions from a global teacher community.",
    "cd_t_334": "The world's largest informal teacher PLN — #EduTwitter, #EduChat and hundreds of subject hashtags connect educators globally.",
    "cd_t_335": "Anonymous, honest teacher discussion — real talk on workload, behaviour, admin and what actually works in classrooms.",
    "cd_t_336": "Free global community of evidence-minded teachers — annual conferences, regional events and online discussions.",
    "cd_t_337": "Free informal teacher unconferences — 7-minute and 2-minute teacher-to-teacher shares, held locally and online worldwide.",
    "cd_t_338": "Local and online Google Educator Groups in 100+ countries — professional learning, events and peer support for Google-using teachers.",
    "cd_t_339": "Free Microsoft educator community — share lessons, earn badges and connect with innovators using Microsoft tools in education.",
    "cd_t_340": "Free Edutopia blogging and discussion community — share your teaching story and read what's working in classrooms worldwide.",
    "cd_t_341": "National Education Association's free member network — professional connections, advocacy tools and peer support for US teachers.",
